@startuml AgentStore-Agent-Run-Flow
!theme plain
title AgentStore — Simulated Agent Run (Tool-Call Trace)
caption How an agent execution works under the hood

skinparam shadowing false
skinparam sequenceArrowThickness 2

actor User
participant "Frontend" as FE
participant "Backend API" as API
participant "Agent Registry" as Reg
participant "Agent Runner" as Runner
participant "Tool Registry" as Tools
participant "Mock Tools" as Mock
database "Trace Log" as Trace

User -> FE : Click "Run Agent"
FE -> API : POST /agents/{id}/run\n{ input }

API -> Reg : get_agent(id)
Reg --> API : agent manifest\n(tools_required, permissions)

API -> Runner : run_agent(id, input)

Runner -> Runner : **Step 1**\nReceive user request
Runner -> Runner : **Step 2**\nIdentify required tools

loop For each required tool
  Runner -> Tools : get_tool(tool_id)
  Tools --> Runner : tool schema +\nmock notes
  Runner -> Mock : call mock tool
  Mock --> Runner : canned response\n(from datasets/)
  Runner -> Runner : **Step 3–4**\nCall tool & process response
end

Runner -> Runner : **Step 5**\nGenerate final answer
Runner -> Trace : **Step 6**\nSave run history + trace

Runner --> API : output + trace
API --> FE : RunResponse
FE --> User : Result + trace viewer

note over Mock
  MVP uses mock data only.
  Real MCP integration
  replaces this in Phase 4.
end note

note over Trace
  Example traces:
  • Email Summarizer
  • GitHub Issue Triage
  • Meeting Notes
end note

@enduml
